{
  "stem": "3659.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So sometimes we stood 12, 14 hours on line to just to get a rubber stamp on a piece of paper.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there were times when you had maybe 300, 400, 500 Jews standing in line in front of these offices.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they would take a truck and just go right into the people and drive into them and just harm and hurt them.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I know it's very difficult for people in this generation, in our generation now, the young people, to understand or to realize what went on.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But the fear that we experienced, which later on I tried to explain to my son, how can I explain to you what fear is if you've never experienced fear?",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "How can I explain to you what pain is unless you have experienced pain?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And words cannot-- and you don't know what hunger is unless you have really been hungry in your life.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] What did you eat in those days?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had to-- again, through bribing, bribery, because they wouldn't sell to Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So you had to find people that you could bribe to buy food for you.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there were only a handful of people that would help you because they didn't want to help a Jew.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was a handful who would do it just to get the money, and there was maybe one or two who would do it out of the goodness of their heart.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And so we just kept on going.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In the meantime, the summer was passing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You know, it was during the summer.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my father found out that there is a school that the-- it was called Israeli [NON-ENGLISH] Kultusgemeinden.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They had school, a little school, classes, that you can learn a trade quickly.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
